Allowance for Credit Losses
The allowance for credit losses increased $379 million from
December 31, 2021 to $14.2 billion at December 31, 2022,
which includ ed a $202 million reserve increase related to the
consumer portfolio and a $177 million reserve increase related
to the commercial portfolio. The increase in the allowance wasprimarily driven by loan growth and a dampened
macroeconomic outlook, partially offset by a reserve release for
reduced pandemic uncertainties.
